<xml-fragment xmlns:npfitlc="NPFIT:HL7:Localisation" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 2 hours.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>An illness or health problem was the main problem.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>User Comments: TEST<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual was not fighting for breath.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The main reason for the assessment was not an allergic reaction, heart attack, chest/upper back pain, probable stroke, recent fit/seizure or suicide attempt.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The main reason for contact was not new confusion, declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia, or ICD shock.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Pathway selected - Nosebleeds without Injury<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual was not feeling faint or dizzy.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The nose was continuing to bleed.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was no nasal foreign body.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Constant pressure had been applied to the soft part of the nose for at least 10 minutes.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Instructions given were: The individual needs to attend a treatment centre within 1 hour.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Directory of Services referral: **TESTING ONLY** DO NOT SEND PATIENTS - ED Test Service for EDDI<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Advice given: Worsening <urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/></xml-fragment>
